    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "An appraisal of Typilobus Stoliczka, 1871 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Leucosioidea), with description of a new family and genus" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.266706>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.266707> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.266706>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Typilobus granulosus Stoliczka, 1871, the type species of Typilobus Stoliczka, 1871, from the Miocene of Pakistan. A, NHMUK In 28638 in dorsal (A 1), ventral (A 2), and posterior (A 3) views; B, NHMUK In 22990 (figured by Withers 1925: pl. 3, figs. 1 – 2) in lateral (B 1), dorsal (B 2), ventral (B 3), posterior (B 4), and frontal (B 5) views; C – D, digital images of Stoliczka (1871: pl. 3, figs. 3, 5) showing male (C) and female (D) specimens. Note that schematic drawings of pleon (C 2, D 2) do not fully correspond to the figures of entire specimens (C 1, D 1). Specimens in A and B are to scale. Scale bar equals 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/266706/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.266707>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Morphological variation shown in several species assigned to Typilobus. A, Typilobus marginatus Morris & Collins, 1991, holotype NHMUK In 62163 in dorsal (A 1) and ventral view (A 2); B – C, Typilobus sadeki Withers, 1925, holotype NHMUK In 22991 (B) and In 22992 (C) in dorsal (B 1, C 1) and ventral views (B 2, C 2); D, Typilobus belli Quayle & Collins, 1981, holotype NHMUK In 61707; E, Typilobus moralejai Müller, 1993, holotype MGSB 51918; F, Typilobus cf. corrodatus Noetling, 1885, BSPG 1981 XI 15. Specimens in E and F were coated with ammonium chloride prior the photography. Scale bar equals 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/266707/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

